We are going to chain three programs. The output of the first program becomes the input of the second, and the output of the second becomes the input of the third.
 However, note that the first program (codeforces_350_B) reads two arrays of integers and produces two lines of output: the first line is an integer, the second is a space-separated string of integers.

 The second program (atcoder_ARC086_B) reads an integer n and then an array of n integers. It then produces output: first the number of operations, then each operation on a line.

 The third program (atcoder_AGC025_A) reads a single integer and outputs a single integer.

 But note: the second program expects input in the form:
   n
   a1 a2 ... an

